data.title: ADT to report Q4 earnings of 22 cents/share on $1.3 billion revenue, annual dividend yield of 2.71%. Investors eye gains.
data.description: ADT Inc. (NYSE: ADT) is set to announce its Q4 earnings on March 2, with analysts predicting earnings of 22 cents per share, up from last year's 20 cents. Revenue for the quarter is estimated to reach $1.3 billion, compared to the previous year's $1.26 billion. A new five-year commercial agreement was recently unveiled by ADT, Origin AI, and Verisure on Feb. 24. ADT's current annual dividend yield stands at 2.71%, equating to a quarterly dividend of 5.5 cents per share. Investors are showing interest in ADT’s dividend potential alongside its recent performance. To achieve $500 monthly earnings from ADT, the yearly target is $6,000, with calculations based on the quarterly dividend amount. Further details can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Argenx SE (NASDAQ: ARGX) beats Q4 earnings forecasts with $8.02 EPS, sales rise to $1.32B, surpassing $1.29B estimate.
data.description: Argenx SE (NASDAQ: ARGX) announced positive Phase 3 ADAPT OCULUS study results for VYVGART in adults with ocular myasthenia gravis (oMG) alongside their fourth-quarter financial report. Earnings were $8.02 per share, higher than the expected $6.02, and sales rose from $761.2 million to $1.32 billion, surpassing the estimated $1.29 billion. CEO Tim Van Hauwermeiren stated that the company had a successful year in 2025, reaching 19,000 global patients with VYVGART, expanding into gMG and CIDP markets, launching a pre-filled syringe, and progressing pipeline development.

data.title: Hifas da Terra, with 25+ years of experience in Europe, launches in the US with science-backed mushroom supplements.
data.description: In Pontevedra, Spain, on February 27, 2026, the European supplement company Hifas da Terra announced its launch in the United States. The brand introduces a new standard for scientifically supported mushroom supplements in the American wellness sector. These supplements are backed by clinical research and offer traceability, setting a benchmark for the market.

data.title: City of Phoenix awards Everytable $3 million Meals on Wheels contract, enhancing food access for senior residents.
data.description: Phoenix, Arizona has awarded a $3 million contract to Everytable, a food company dedicated to providing fresh, scratch-cooked meals to all residents. The contract aims to enhance food access and community care for senior residents in the city. This initiative is set to bring crucial support and resources to seniors, promoting their well-being and access to nutritious meals. The partnership between the City of Phoenix and Everytable signifies a significant step towards addressing the needs of the senior population and improving overall quality of life in the community.

data.title: AEHL confirms $1 million Bitcoin purchase, launching "Genius Plan" - company's official implementation phase.
data.description: Antelope Enterprise Holdings Limited has announced the completion of its initial $1 million Bitcoin (BTC) purchase, signaling the start of the implementation phase of their strategic initiative dubbed the "Genius Plan." The milestone transaction solidifies the company's commitment to this new direction.

data.title: Enzon Pharmaceuticals extends exchange offer for Series C Preferred Stock to March 9, 2026. Offer expires after 11:59 p.m.
data.description: Enzon Pharmaceuticals, Inc. has extended the expiration date for its exchange offer to holders of Series C Non-Convertible Redeemable Preferred Stock. The offer allows holders to exchange their Series C Preferred Stock for Enzon's Common Stock. The new expiration date is one minute after 11:59 p.m. Eastern Time on March 9, 2026, unless further extended. Enzon Pharmaceuticals, Inc. trades on OTCQB under the symbol ENZN.

data.title: Callan JMB Inc. announces participation in iAccess Alpha Virtual Best Ideas Spring Investment Conference on March 10-11, 2026.
data.description: On February 27, 2026, in Spring Branch, Texas, Callan JMB Inc. (NASDAQ: CJMB), a company specializing in integrative logistics for the healthcare industry and emergency management agencies, disclosed its involvement in the iAccess Alpha Virtual Best Ideas Spring Investment Conference scheduled for March 10-11, 2026. Callan JMB offers services such as fulfillment, storage, monitoring, and cold chain logistics.

data.title: Hip-hop artist B-Cide to drop concept album MonSter on March 1, 2026, after two decades in the industry.
data.description: In Utica, New York, on February 27, 2026, Bob "B-Cide" Cardillo, an independent hip-hop artist, announced that he will be launching his latest concept album titled MonSter on March 1, 2026. This album marks a significant milestone in his music career that has extended over 20 years, characterized by his dedication to independent music and extensive grassroots touring. This release is highly anticipated by his fanbase, and they eagerly await the unique musical experience he promises to deliver.

data.title: Tequity advised SimplyPHP's acquisition by TLM, a Canadian tech company, with SimplyPHP founded in 2010.
data.description: In February 27, 2026, Tequity Advisors served as the sole financial advisor to SimplyPHP, a Canadian firm specializing in senior PHP development and staffing services, during its acquisition by TLM, a Canadian company focused on technology product development. Established in 2010, SimplyPHP has established a strong presence in the market. The acquisition marks a significant milestone for both companies, reflecting the growing trend of mergers and acquisitions in the technology sector. This deal underscores the value placed on SimplyPHP's expertise and services by TLM.
